          "title": "It began as simple entertainment",
          "autor": "Enviada por Izabel Meira de Castro  (Corumbá, MS) em 15 de Junho de 2012",
          "excerpt": "Well, my name is Izabel, I began with a simple entertainment, and the, me and my son got...",
          "content": "<p>Well, my name is Izabel, I began with a simple entertainment, and the, me and my son got accustomed. We had the idea to make a June party for children. We initiated and intend to continue only with children. Its ten years already. And then I said to my son. “My son, here is a separated street. Let’s make a party here? “Ok mom, it’s time to do”. “No, we will manage St. John will help us”. With nine I managed to do my St. John. <br>\n<br>\nWe pitched tents, prepared the dance, the “quadrilha”, and went down to the port. The community helps, each one brings a bit of rice, something, and we prepare food for children. Few persons appeared, but St. John gave a hand to us. Today we are thriving a little more, step by step. And each year I make I provide my St. John with the altar. <br>\n<br>\nEvery year, four straight years, taking St. John from the andor to place Him to the altar. His neck got loose in my hand. Four straight years. Once my sister was putting him in the andor and broke it, too. Then we got a borrowed new one, mounted on the andor and went to the port, came back, and when I tried to touch his head, it fell off. I don’t know, I would like to understand his mystery, for four years. Then I spoke to my mother “mother I don’t know, St. John never wants to stay in the altar”. Since then I began to get and donate, I ascend the port, and the first person I see, I say “its here, a present by St. John for you”. I have another andor made or borrow another saint. We don’t say of buying, but borrowing or donating. <br>\n<br>\nI want this tradition to continue forever, for, we began frolicking and this became a great reality. I put much faith in St. John, in all the saints, mainly Our Lady Aparecida, my Cosme and Damian, my St. John the Baptist. I believe very much in God’s things. <br>\n<br>\nMy sister Luzia, had cancer, excised a breast. But every year I ask St. John to provide health, I think that I obtained that grace that is why I go on. She is ok, she has nothing. She is very well thanks to God and Saint John. And we started like this, kidding; it has been 10 years since I broke my foot.</p>"
