          "content": "<p>My name is Pedro Paulo Miranda, and I am 48 years old, and in our community the St. John’s party has been carried out for 47 years. Just here, in front to the Spirit Center, still exists the house where my parents lived in the year of 1964, where I was born, feeling sick, I already… by the physician, the primitive medicine of Pantanal, and that night, that day, was St. John’s day, 23 to 24, June. <br>\n<br>\nWhen my mother called my aunt, her sister Inês, to christen me, I was not already christened, “He will die, he is ill, he’s…” Then, for not dying pagan there was a baptism before I had the last (…) and deemed dead. <br>\n<br>\nAfter the baptism I had bouts and practically lost all life signals. That moment, on our street, Major Gama, a procession was passing by, St. John Baptist one singing, and praising persons bearing the andor, the image of St. John to the Paraguay River. And, of course, just like any mother taken with despair, my mother came running from inside home and heard people sing: “God saves you John”. And she didn’t know that John was always miraculous and justice-maker saint and my mother fell on her knees, crying, any mother would do that, in her despair. And spoke, if St. John Baptist intercedes to God, to the spirits, and give health, returned my health, she would make the feast, henceforth. Then my aunt, whose house is near, very next to mine, came and said. <br>\n<br>\n“Get up, get up”, I called her Minda. Get up; get up, Minda get up and she didn’t want to go. “Get up, the<br>\nboy waked up, he’s awake. At this moment she entered the house and noticed I was awake. I grew up attending the party, and later, already understanding, mother said. “I began this feast for your cause” And my love for the party increased more and more in the decades of 70 and 80, the feast was made by casting lots, the organization,<br>\ncollaboration of each feaster, the feast that offered himself to be a feaster on Saint Peters’ night, after lowering the mast, then put the two hats, then the raffle in presence of the audience, behind here. Two hats, one with the name of the feaster, and other with the function he was to do in the party next year. It happens this way. <br>\n<br>\nWe chose by sortition the persons that would take care of the straw, the arrayal, the firewood, the<br>\nbanners, to make sweets (a certain amount, of course), liquor, quentão. All those things are offered freely in the party. The feast took place in the backyard, but afterwards, they increased and began to occur in the street. We through of stopping, but we realized we had 20/22 years of achievement of the feast. Then the community: “no, no, we are here to collaborate, to help in what is necessary, what’s possible”! I realized the party belonged no more only to the spirit center, to became property of all the religious community, to the population in general. The religious side, today, that from spirit Tent finished with this thing. Of (…) run by my sister Rita Joana, with the decease of my mother, Carlinda Miranda, she was who cared the Tent, Carlinda, named after Carmen<br>\nMiranda and my brother Manoel Divino and I am the responsible for all religious aspects and for the works that happen here in the Tent. Up to present day finish (…) well, thank you all. May God save Saint John!</p>"
